<?xml version="1.0" encoding="koi8-r"?>
<!--
    Rune-spell registry (issue.runes-migrate).

    Each <spell> entry binds an ESpell text_id to a list of rune vnums plus
    the minimum caster level. Replaces lib/misc/runes.lst, which the legacy
    InitSpellLevels() parser in pc_classes.cpp used to read.

    runes= is a |-separated list of integer rune vnums; the legacy format had
    a fixed 4-slot ceiling, the new schema accepts arbitrary length.
    level= is clamped to [1, 34] at load time (the legacy invariant).

    Disabled spells are kept below as ordinary XML comments (lines that started
    with ";" in runes.lst); the data is preserved for future re-enabling.

    Reload at runtime via `reload runes` (issue.runes-migrate retired the legacy
    `reload rune_levels` path through the standard cfg_manager).
-->
